oai_dc:dc.dc:title: LAND RECLAMATION AND GROIN-BUILDING IN THE TIDAL PLATS
oai_dc:dc.dc:creator: Erchinger, Hele Focken
oai_dc:dc.dc:subject: land reclamation
tidal flats
groin
groin construction
oai_dc:dc.dc:description: Along the North Sea eoast of Germany there are two large areas where land reclamation work in the tidal flats is being carried out. One is on the coast of Schleswig- Holstem and the other in Ostfriesland, on the coast and along the estuary of the river Ems near the border with the Netherlands. Conditions and working methods for land reclamation in tidal flats as well as the development of new groin constructions on the Ostfriesian coast are described below.
oai_dc:dc.dc:source: Coastal Engineering Proceedings; No. 12 (1970): Proceedings of 12th Conference on Coastal Engineering, Washington, D.C., 1970.; 66
